pullRequest.body:
This PR:
* bumps to lean-toolchain to `v4.5.0-rc1`
* bumps the Std and Aesop dependencies to their versions using `v4.5.0-rc1`
* merge the already reviewed changes from the `bump/v4.5.0` branch
  * adaptations for leanprover/lean4#2923 in #9011
  * adaptations for leanprover/lean4#2973 in #9161
  * adaptations for leanprover/lean4#2964 in #9176

As commented in https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/9011/files#r1426012984, this looks a bit odd; I think this test was intended to test the error message for `at *`, not to succeed.

The context here is https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/pull/2917.

The test was previously checking for an error message which we decided shouldn't be produced at all!
I've changed the tactic back to `abel_nf at *`, and added a comment explaining the history.
